      "id": "20440176_370ca288",
      "file_path": "dbc-client/misc/dbc-client",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 22,
      "message": "Needs some additional documentation.  What does the script expect to find in the various \"*.json\" files that it's processing?  If you're just expecting those files to contain payloads that meet the DBC API, provide a pointer to the relevant parts of the API documentation.  (If I'm reading the code correctly [and I might not be], you're expecting some additional information about publishers and subscribers in the \"feeds\" JSON files.) \n\nAlso--even more importantly--document what is being saved in the response files.  Another script/program is going to have to read those responses and inject some of the information into the configuration for a microservice.  Whoever writes that script/program needs to know what's in the responses.",
